HAL 9000计算机  它可以「复制」...
The HAL 9000 computer, which can reproduce,

356
01:01:09,000 --> 01:01:12,110
不过有些专家更喜欢称之为「模仿」
though some experts still prefer to use the word "mimic",

357
01:01:12,110 --> 01:01:14,580
...人类大脑中的大多数活动
most of the activities of the human brain

358
01:01:14,580 --> 01:01:18,680
并且其运行速度和可靠性不可估量
and with incalculably greater speed and reliability.

359
01:01:18,920 --> 01:01:22,730
我们接下来采访了HAL 9000计算机
We next spoke with the HAL 9000 computer

360
01:01:22,730 --> 01:01:25,610
我们得知  它也被称作哈尔
whom, we learned, one addresses as "Hal."

361
01:01:26,350 --> 01:01:28,860
下午好  哈尔  一切都好吗
Good afternoon, Hal. How's everything going?

362
01:01:28,870 --> 01:01:32,930
下午好  艾莫先生  一切都十分顺利
Good afternoon, Mr. Amer. Everything is going extremely well.

363
01:01:32,970 --> 01:01:35,960
哈尔  此次任务你责任重大
Hal, you have an enormous responsibility on this mission.

364
01:01:35,960 --> 01:01:36,580
从很多方面来说
In many ways

365
01:01:36,580 --> 01:01:40,690
你身上的担子或许是这次任务中最重的
perhaps the greatest responsibility of any single mission element.

366
01:01:40,700 --> 01:01:43,740
你是飞船的大脑以及中枢神经系统
You're the brain and central nervous system of the ship.

367
01:01:43,740 --> 01:01:45,270
你的职责包括
And your responsibilities include

368
01:01:45,270 --> 01:01:47,680
看护休眠中的航天员
watching over the men in hibernation.

369
01:01:47,680 --> 01:01:50,930
这会让你缺乏自信心吗
Does this ever cause you any lack of confidence?

370
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:53,180
我这么说吧  艾莫先生
Let me put it this way, Mr. Amer.

371
01:01:53,590 --> 01:01:58,060
9000系列是有史以来最可靠的计算机
The 9000 Series is the most reliable computer ever made.

372
01:01:58,590 --> 01:02:00,130
9000系列计算机
No 9000 computer

373
01:02:00,130 --> 01:02:03,590
从未犯过错误  也从未歪曲过信息
has ever made a mistake or distorted information.

374
01:02:04,070 --> 01:02:07,470
无论如何形容定义  我们都是
We are all, by any practical definition of the words,

375
01:02:07,630 --> 01:02:10,890
万无一失  不会出错的
foolproof and incapable of error.

376
01:02:11,200 --> 01:02:13,950
哈尔  尽管你具备高度智能
Hal, despite your enormous intellect,

377
01:02:13,950 --> 01:02:17,180
你曾因为需要依靠人类来执行操作
are you ever frustrated by your dependence on people

378
01:02:17,180 --> 01:02:18,530
而懊恼过吗
to carry out actions?

379
01:02:18,530 --> 01:02:20,660
完全没有
Not in the slightest bit.

380
01:02:21,060 --> 01:02:23,280
我喜欢与人类共事
I enjoy working with people.

381
01:02:23,370 --> 01:02:27,400
我与普尔博士和鲍曼博士保持着高度活跃的关系
I have a stimulating relationship with Dr. Poole and Dr. Bowman.

382
01:02:28,050 --> 01:02:29,620
我的任务职责
My mission responsibilities

383
01:02:29,630 --> 01:02:32,790
囊括了飞船所有的运行操作
range over the entire operation of the ship

384
01:02:32,850 --> 01:02:35,380
所以我一直忙得不可开交
so I am constantly occupied.

385
01:02:35,930 --> 01:02:39,190
我也在尽我所能
I am putting myself to the fullest possible use

386
01:02:39,630 --> 01:02:42,160
我想这对任何一个有意识的实体来说
which is all, I think, that any conscious entity

387
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:43,900
都是梦寐以求的
can ever hope to do.

388
01:02:45,080 --> 01:02:48,580
普尔博士  在这将近一年的时间里
Dr. Poole, what's it like living for the better part of a year

389
01:02:48,580 --> 01:02:51,140
一直与哈尔近距离接触是什么感觉
in such close proximity with Hal?

390
01:02:52,290 --> 01:02:54,730
跟你之前对他的描述差不多
Well, it's pretty close to what you said about him earlier.

391
01:02:54,730 --> 01:02:57,010
他就像是第六名航天员
He's just like a sixth member of the crew...

392
01:02:57,020 --> 01:02:59,680
我很快就习惯了他会说话的事实
very quickly get adjusted to the idea that he talks,

393
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:03,100
会把他当作一个人来看待
and you think of him really just as another person.

394
01:03:03,420 --> 01:03:04,920
在与计算机交流的过程中
In talking to the computer,

395
01:03:04,920 --> 01:03:08,890
有人感觉到他能做出情绪反应
one gets the sense that he's capable of emotional responses.

396
01:03:08,900 --> 01:03:11,340
比如  当我问到他的能力时
For example, when I asked him about his abilities,

397
01:03:11,340 --> 01:03:13,190
他回答说自己是精准完美的
I sensed a certain pride in his answer

398
01:03:13,190 --> 01:03:15,630
我从中感到了一丝得意
about his accuracy and perfection.

399
01:03:15,670 --> 01:03:18,920
你认为哈尔具有真情实感吗
Do you believe that Hal has genuine emotions?

400
01:03:19,780 --> 01:03:22,150
他表现得像是有真情实感
Well, he acts like he has genuine emotions.

401
01:03:22,950 --> 01:03:24,120
当然了  他的程序是这么设定的
Of course, he's programmed that way

402
01:03:24,120 --> 01:03:26,290
好让我们能更加方便地与他交流
to make it easier for us to talk to him.

403
01:03:26,780 --> 01:03:29,220
但是至于他有没有感情
But as to whether or not he has real feelings

404
01:03:29,220 --> 01:03:32,030
我觉得没有人能给出确切的答案
is something I don't think anyone can truthfully answer.

405
01:03:57,220 --> 01:03:58,890
打扰一下  弗兰克
Excuse me, Frank.

406
01:03:59,430 --> 01:04:00,680
怎么了  哈尔
What is it, Hal?

407
01:04:00,680 --> 01:04:03,450
我们收到了你父母传来的消息
We've got the transmission from your parents coming in.

408
01:04:04,950 --> 01:04:06,320
好
Fine.

409
01:04:06,560 --> 01:04:09,140
就在这播放吧  把我移过去一点
Put it on here, please. Take me in a bit.

410
01:04:09,140 --> 01:04:10,570
好的
Certainly.

411
01:04:23,750 --> 01:04:25,410
-你好  弗兰克  -生日快乐  亲爱的
- Hello, Frank. - Happy birthday, darling.

412
01:04:25,410 --> 01:04:27,790
生日快乐  年年有今日  岁岁有今朝
Happy birthday. Many happy returns of the day..

413
01:04:27,790 --> 01:04:29,490
-再升高一点  哈尔  -很高兴听到你和大卫都很好
- A bit higher, Hal. - Glad to hear you and Dave are well.

414
01:04:29,490 --> 01:04:31,810
你妈妈和我也都很好
Mother and I are both feeling wonderful too.

415
01:04:31,820 --> 01:04:33,530
雷和莎莉本来也准备来跟你通话的
Ray and Sally were going to be here too

416
01:04:33,530 --> 01:04:36,570
但雷的背伤突然又犯了
but at the last minute Ray's back went bad on him again.

417
01:04:36,580 --> 01:04:38,940
-你喜欢这个蛋糕吗  -看起来很棒吧
- How do you like your cake, dear? - Looks great, huh?

418
01:04:38,940 --> 01:04:40,520
可惜你不能和我们一起共享
Sorry you can't join us.

419
01:04:40,730 --> 01:04:42,480
前几天我遇到了鲍勃
I ran into Bob the other day.

420
01:04:42,490 --> 01:04:44,580
他说一定要让我代为祝你生日快乐
He said be sure to wish you happy birthday.

421
01:04:44,580 --> 01:04:47,460
我的全体学生也让我务必向你问好
All my students made me promise to send their best wishes too.

422
01:04:47,470 --> 01:04:49,640
他们在教室里总是谈到你  弗兰克
You know they talk about you all the time in the classroom, Frank.

423
01:04:49,640 --> 01:04:52,080
你成了二年级学生心中的大名人了
You're a big celebrity in the second grade.

424
01:04:52,700 --> 01:04:54,410
上周我们上了电视
You know we were on television last week.

425
01:04:54,420 --> 01:04:56,840
没错  你妈妈和我还有大卫的父母
Oh yes, yes. Your mother and I and Dave's parents

426
01:04:56,840 --> 01:04:59,830
被问到我们如何看待自己的杰出的儿子
were interviewed about what we thought of our illustrious sons.

427
01:04:59,830 --> 01:05:01,520
你可以想象得出我们是怎么回答的
Heh, you can imagine what we told them.

428
01:05:01,770 --> 01:05:03,480
好像节目下周四就会播出
I think it's being broadcast next Thursday.

429
01:05:03,480 --> 01:05:05,250
或许你能收听到
Perhaps you'll be able to listen in.

430
01:05:05,250 --> 01:05:07,270
对了  埃琳娜和比尔的事  我们也很激动
Oh, we were thrilled about Elaine and Bill, dear.

431
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:08,840
我很乐意帮你给他们买礼物
I'll be glad to get the present for you

432
01:05:08,840 --> 01:05:10,830
不过请告诉我预算是多少
but please tell me how much I can spend.

433
01:05:11,220 --> 01:05:14,390
对了  弗兰克  你的AGS19薪水
Oh, yes, Frank, about your AGS-19 payments...

434
01:05:14,390 --> 01:05:16,160
我应该都帮你处理好了
I think I straightened it out for you.

435
01:05:16,160 --> 01:05:18,330
我昨天跟休斯顿那边的财务室谈过了
I talked to the accounting office in Houston yesterday

436
01:05:18,330 --> 01:05:19,890
他们说下个月你应该就能收到
and they said you should be receiving

437
01:05:19,890 --> 01:05:22,150
涨过之后的工资了
your higher rates of pay by next month.

438
01:05:23,380 --> 01:05:25,810
好了  弗兰克  我没什么要说的了
Well, Frank, I can't think of anything else to say, now.

439
01:05:25,820 --> 01:05:26,710
代我们向大卫问好
Give our love to Dave.

440
01:05:26,710 --> 01:05:29,100
没错  记得问好
Oh yes. Be sure to give him our best regards.

441
01:05:30,140 --> 01:05:32,470
我们衷心地祝你生日快乐
We wish you the very happiest of birthdays.

442
01:05:32,470 --> 01:05:33,540
上帝保佑
God bless!

443
01:05:33,540 --> 01:05:35,230
一切顺利  儿子
All the best, son.

444
