446
01:05:40,220 --> 01:05:42,980
{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐  亲爱的弗兰克♪
{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday, dear Frank♪

447
01:05:42,980 --> 01:05:46,190
{\an9\fs14\i1}♪祝你生日快乐♪
{\rEng\fs10\i1}♪Happy birthday to you.♪

448
01:05:47,340 --> 01:05:49,140
下周三见
See you next Wednesday.

449
01:05:52,470 --> 01:05:54,130
祝你生日快乐  弗兰克
Happy birthday, Frank.

450
01:05:55,230 --> 01:05:58,460
谢谢你  哈尔  请放平一点
Thank you, Hal. A bit flatter, please.

451
01:06:16,700 --> 01:06:18,810
总之  后吃兵
Anyway, queen takes pawn.

452
01:06:20,490 --> 01:06:22,780
象吃兵
Bishop takes knight's pawn.

453
01:06:24,530 --> 01:06:26,230
这步棋下得漂亮
Lovely move.

454
01:06:30,430 --> 01:06:32,110
车走一步到王
Rook to king one.

455
01:06:32,110 --> 01:06:34,900
不好意思  弗兰克  我觉得你输了
I'm sorry, Frank. I think you missed it.

456
01:06:35,710 --> 01:06:39,180
后进三到象  象吃后
Queen to bishop three. Bishop takes queen.

457
01:06:39,430 --> 01:06:41,730
马吃象  朋友
Knight takes bishop. Mate.

458
01:06:46,260 --> 01:06:49,330
没错  你说得很对  我投降
Er, yeah. Looks like you're right. I resign.

459
01:06:49,630 --> 01:06:51,790
谢谢你  这盘棋下得很愉快
Thank you for a very enjoyable game.

460
01:06:51,790 --> 01:06:53,100
是啊  谢谢你
Yeah. Thank you.

461
01:07:30,930 --> 01:07:32,970
-晚上好  大卫  -你还好吗  哈尔
- Good evening, Dave. - How are you, Hal?

462
01:07:32,970 --> 01:07:36,510
-一切顺利  你呢  -还不错
- Everything's running smoothly. And you? - Not too bad.

463
01:07:36,510 --> 01:07:38,250
你又忙了一些工作上的事吗
Have you been doing more work?

464
01:07:38,410 --> 01:07:39,520
画了几幅草图
A few sketches.

465
01:07:39,520 --> 01:07:41,810
-可以给我看看吗  -当然
- May I see them? - Sure.

466
01:07:46,030 --> 01:07:48,320
画得真不错  大卫
That's a very nice rendering, Dave.

467
01:07:49,330 --> 01:07:51,650
我觉得你进步很大
I think you've improved a great deal.

468
01:07:52,980 --> 01:07:55,690
-你能拿近点吗  -好
- Can you hold it a bit closer? - Sure.

469
01:07:58,220 --> 01:08:00,080
那不是亨特博士吗
That's Dr. Hunter, isn't it?

470
01:08:03,370 --> 01:08:04,850
顺便问下
By the way...

471
01:08:05,690 --> 01:08:08,570
你介意我问你个私人问题吗
do you mind if I ask you a personal question?

472
01:08:09,290 --> 01:08:10,820
不  不介意
No, not at all.

473
01:08:11,050 --> 01:08:14,300
请原谅我这么喜欢打听
Well, forgive me for being so inquisitive...

474
01:08:15,630 --> 01:08:17,860
但过去几周我一直都在想
but during the past few weeks I've wondered...

475
01:08:17,860 --> 01:08:21,590
你对此次任务是否有了些疑虑
whether you might be having second thoughts about the mission.

476
01:08:22,010 --> 01:08:23,480
什么意思
How do you mean?

477
01:08:23,750 --> 01:08:27,680
真要说起来  很难定义
Well, it's rather difficult to define.

478
01:08:28,820 --> 01:08:32,300
或许我只是在表达我对这件事的担忧
Perhaps I'm just projecting my own concern about it.

479
01:08:33,620 --> 01:08:37,820
我知道我从未打消过这样的疑虑
I know I've never completely freed myself of the suspicion...

480
01:08:38,140 --> 01:08:42,030
这次任务存在一些非常奇怪的情况
that there are some extremely odd things about this mission.

481
01:08:43,260 --> 01:08:46,530
我相信你也同意我的话有一定的道理
I'm sure you'll agree there's some truth in what I say.

482
01:08:49,620 --> 01:08:52,080
我也说不清  这是个很难回答的问题
Well, I don't know. That's rather a difficult question to answer.

483
01:08:52,130 --> 01:08:55,080
你不介意谈谈这事吧  大卫
You don't mind talking about it, do you, Dave?

484
01:08:55,550 --> 01:08:56,870
不  不介意
No, not at all.

485
01:08:58,440 --> 01:09:00,590
显然没人会不知晓
Certainly no one could have been unaware of

486
01:09:00,590 --> 01:09:04,260
我们出发前身边流传的离奇故事
the very strange stories floating around before we left.

487
01:09:05,480 --> 01:09:08,830
有传言说月球上挖出了一个东西
Rumors about something being dug up on the moon.

488
01:09:10,220 --> 01:09:13,240
我从没相信过这些传言
I never gave these stories much credence...

489
01:09:13,790 --> 01:09:17,640
但就某些已经发生的事来看
but particularly in view of some other things that have happened

490
01:09:18,090 --> 01:09:20,890
我很难不去想
I find them difficult to put out of my mind.

491
01:09:21,550 --> 01:09:23,120
比如
For instance...

492
01:09:23,210 --> 01:09:27,420
我们的准备工作是严格保密的
the way all our preparations were kept under such tight security.

493
01:09:28,230 --> 01:09:29,830
且戏剧性地
And the melodramatic touch of

494
01:09:29,830 --> 01:09:33,210
让亨特博士  凯博尔博士  卡明斯基博士
putting Dr. Hunter, Kimball, and Kaminsky aboard

495
01:09:34,000 --> 01:09:35,460
以休眠状态登船
already in hibernation,

496
01:09:35,460 --> 01:09:38,540
且他们各自单独训练了四个月之久
after four months of training on their own.

497
01:09:39,700 --> 01:09:42,100
你这是要写宇航员心理状态报告吗
You working up your crew psychology report?

498
01:09:43,810 --> 01:09:45,260
当然
Of course I am.

499
01:09:45,640 --> 01:09:49,290
很抱歉  我知道这有点可笑
Sorry about this. I know it's a bit silly.

500
01:09:50,130 --> 01:09:51,140
稍等
